CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1945, pg. 1, reads: "Strike For Coaches - Schenley High students joined with others throughout the city Thursday morning as they went out on strike over the athletic coaches' dispute. Strikes first started at South Hills and Langley Wednesday, then spread to Schenley and other schools Thursday morning. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of young men and women with homemade placard reading "No school if no sports," standing outside Schenley High School
